Sentencas: Cobalt-free composite cathodes consisting of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta-xCe(0.9)Pr(0.1)O(2-delta) (PSFO-xCPO, x = 0-50 wt%) have been synthesized using a one-pot method.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, thermal expansion coefficient, conductivity, and polarization resistance (R-p) have been used to characterize the PSFO-xCPO cathodes.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore the discharge performance of the Ni-SSZ/SSZ/GDC/PSFO-xCPO cells has been measured.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The experimental results indicate that the PSFO-xCPO composite materials fully consist of PSFO and CPO phases and posses a porous microstructure.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of PSFO-xCPO decreases with the increase of CPO content, but R-p of PSFO-40CPO shows the smallest value amongst all the samples.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power density of single cells with a PSFO-40CPO composite cathode is significantly improved compared with that of the PSFO cathode, exhibiting 0.43, 0.75, 1.08 and 1.30 W cm(-2) at 650, 700, 750 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, single cells with the PSFO-40CPO composite cathode show a stable performance with no obvious degradation over 100 h when operating at 750 degrees C. Copyright (C) 2016, Hydrogen Energy Publications, LLC.
Titulo: Synthesis of Pr0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ-xCe0.9Pr0.1O2-δ cobalt-free composite cathodes by a one-pot method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
